ente Santa Fe|Independiente SF]]      | caps9  = 16 | goals9  = 0\n| years10        = 2005      | clubs10 = [[Deportivo Cali]]                               | caps10 = 15 | goals10 = 0\n| years11        = 2006      | clubs11 = [[CF Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]] | caps11 = 3  | goals11 = 0\n| years12        = 2006      | clubs12 = [[Universitario de Sucre]]                       | caps12 = 9  | goals12 = 0\n| years13        = 2007      | clubs13 = [[Deportes Melipilla]]                           | caps13 = 22 | goals13 = 0\n| years14        = 2008      | clubs14 = [[Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez FBC|Jos\u00e9 G\u00e1lvez]]                  | caps14 = 18 | goals14 = 0\n| years15        = 2008      | clubs15 = [[Club Blooming|Blooming]]                       | caps15 = 13 | goals15 = 0\n| years16        = 2009      | clubs16 = [[Club Bol\u00edvar|Bol\u00edvar]]                         | caps16 = 8  | goals16 = 0\n| years17        = 2010      | clubs17 = [[Deportivo Italia]]                             | caps17 = 11 | goals17 = 0\n| years18        = 2010      | clubs18 = [[Oriente Petrolero]]                            | caps18 = 9  | goals18 = 0\n| totalcaps      = 326\n| totalgoals     = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 1998\u20132004\n| nationalteam1  = [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 26\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate       = 25 November 2010\n| ntupdate       = 4 November 2012\n}}\n\n'''Jos\u00e9 Carlos Fern\u00e1ndez Gonz\u00e1lez''' ({{IPA-es|xo\u02c8se \u02c8ka\u027elos fe\u027e\u02c8nande\u03b8}}, born 24 January 1971) is a [[Bolivian people|Bolivian]] retired [[Association football|football]] goalkeeper who is currently active as [[director of football]] of Bolivian club [[Club Bol\u00edvar|Bol\u00edvar]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nFern\u00e1ndez developed his football skills at the prestigious [[T|Tahuichi Academy]], where he received a full scholarship to go to the United States and play while in college. After he finished school, he pursued a career as a professional goalkeeper.\n\n===International success at Cali===\nIn his home country, Fern\u00e1ndez played for important teams such as [[Oriente Petrolero]], [[Club Blooming|Blooming]] and [[Club Bol\u00edvar|Bol\u00edvar]]. He also went abroad to play for [[C\u00f3rdoba CF]] in Spain, [[Chiapas F.C.|Jaguares]] and [[Tiburones Rojos de Veracruz|Veracruz]] in Mexico, [[New England Revolution]] in the MLS, [[Independiente Santa Fe]] and [[Deportivo Cali]] from Colombia.\n\n===Deportes Melipilla===\n\n===Late career===\n\n==International career==\nHe has been capped for the [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivian national team]] on 26 occasions,<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bol-recintlp.html Appearances for Bolivia National Team] {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5hSQcHr8I?url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bol-recintlp.html |date=11 June 2009 }} - RSSSF</ref> having participated in [[Copa Am\u00e9rica 1999]] and [[Copa Am\u00e9rica 2004|2004]] among the most important tournaments he took part in. He represented his country in 9 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches and at the [[1999 Confederations Cup]].<ref>{{FIFA|154434}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Blooming\n* [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] (2): [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano 1998|1998]], [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano 1999|1999]]\n\n;Bol\u00edvar\n* [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] (1): [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano 2002|2002]]\n* [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano|Torneo de Apertura]] (1): [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano 2009|2009]]\n\n;Deportivo Cali\n* [[Colombian Primera A|Torneo Finalizaci\u00f3n]] (1): [[Copa Mustang II 2005|2005]]\n\n;Oriente Petrolero\n* [[Liga de F\u00fatbol Profesional Boliviano|Torneo de Clausura]] (1): 2010\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT|863|Jos\