{"title_page": "Michael Madana Kama Rajan", "text_new": "{{short description|1990 film by Singeetam Srinivasa Rao}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Michael Madana Kama Rajan\n| image          = Michael Madana Kama Rajan.jpg\n| alt            = L to R: Madhan and Chakkubai, Kameswaran and Thirupurasundari, Shalini and Raju\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]\n| producer       = Meena Panchu Arunachalam\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* [[Kamal Haasan]]\n* [[Crazy Mohan]] {{small|(dialogue)}}\n}}\n| story          = Kamal Haasan<br /> Kader Kashmiri\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* Kamal Haasan\n* [[Urvashi (actress)|Urvasi]]\n* [[Rupini (actress)|Rupini]]\n* [[Kushboo]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cinematography = [[B. C. Gowrishankar]]\n| editing        = D. Vasu\n| studio         = [[Panchu Arunachalam|P. A. Art Productions]]\n| released       = 17 October 1990\n| runtime        = 167 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n\n'''''Michael Madana Kama Rajan''''' is a 1990 [[Tamil language]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]] and written by [[Kamal Haasan]], with [[Crazy Mohan]] penning the dialogues.\n\nThe film also feature a large [[ensemble cast]] alongside Kamal Haasan, [[Urvasi (actress)|Urvasi]], [[Rupini (actress)|Rupini]], [[Kushboo]] played the female leads, while [[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]], [[Delhi Ganesh]], [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]], [[Venniradai Moorthy]], [[SN Lakshmi]], [[Jayabharathi]], [[R. N. Jayagopal]], [[Nagesh]], [[Praveen Kumar (actor)|Praveen Kumar]] and [[Santhana Bharathi]] playing other significant roles. The film was a blockbuster and completed 175-day run at the box office.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nThe film tells a story of [[quadruplets]], Michael, Mathanagopal, Kameshwaran, and Raju, all played by Kamal Haasan. Kamal distinguished each of those characters with his body language and language lingo. Michael has a husky voice and an aggressive demeanor, Mathana has a [[British English|British accent]] with a sophisticated upper-class personality, Kameshwaran speaks [[Palakkad]] Tamil and has a naive, childish personality while Raju speaks [[Madras Tamil]] and has an outgoing, cheerful personality; all in keeping with their diverse upbringing as per the plot. The character played by an actress [[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]] was well received by the audience and still considered as one of the best comic role played ever by a heroine. The film was dubbed in Telugu as ''Michael Mathana Kama Raju''.\n\n== Plot ==\n{{Long plot|section|date=February 2017}}\n\nVenugopal is a wealthy industrialist. His wife Sushila gives birth to quadruplets, but his brother Nandagopal sends goons to kill the four children. But the leader of the goons doesn't want to kill the babies, so he adopts one (Michael), leaves one in an orphanage (Raju), one in a temple (Kameshwaran) who is picked by Palakkad Mani Iyer, and one (Madhan) in a car that belongs to Venugopal.\n\n30 years later, Madhan is now a London-educated businessman and the \"adopted\" son of Venugopal. He returns from London after his father's death to take over the business. But unbeknownst to him, Venugopal's car accident was planned by Nandagopal and Ramu for the want of his father's property. But Venugopal's will has named Madhan as the heir to all his wealth.\n\nMeanwhile, Michael has become a petty criminal like his foster father. While escaping from the police, they accidentally cause a fire in an art gallery where an artist Shalini is conducting an exhibition. A firefighter Raju saves Shalini and her paintings, and they fall in love after she gifts him a rice painting of Taj Mahal.\n\nKameshwaran is introduced as a cook for weddings and special events. He meets Thirupurasundari and her kleptomaniac grandmother. After a series of hilarious interactions, Kameshwaran and Thirupu fall in love and their wedding is being arranged\n\nAn unknown woman telephones Madhan tells him that his father's death was not an accident, and asks him to meet her in Chennai. After being distracted by a young girl named Chakkubai and her mother Gangubai, Madhan finally meets Sushila who called him. But he doesn't know that she is his real mother.\n\nWhile escaping from goons sent by Nandagopal and Ramu, Madhan meets Raju who fights the goons and saves him. He asks Raju to impersonate him for a while in Bangalore till he investigates his father's death in Chennai. Raju (while pretending to be Madhan) meets Shalini and her father who are also going to Bangalore, and invites them to stay with him.\n\nMichael is hired to kill Madhan and finds out that he is in Chennai. Meanwhile Madhan and Chakkubai have fallen in love and he presents her with a ring, but they are spied on by Michael and his father. Sushila meets Madhan again and reveals that his father in alive but is mentally unstable after the accident. Michael and his foster father arrive at the scene and kidnap all of them to a mountain cabin near Bangalore.\n\nOn the day of Kameshwaran's wedding, Avinashi sees him and asks him to impersonate Madhan to get 6 lakhs from his locker. Back in Madhan's house in Bangalore,\nRaju and Shalini meet and profess their love for one another. Michael (also dressed as Madhan) and his father arrive at Madhan's house to loot it. Michael sees Raju, mistakes him for Madhan and thinks that Madhan has escaped from the cabin. He knocks Raju unconscious.\n\nAvinashi sees the unconscious Raju, assumes it was the effect of his drugged soup, and brings Kameshwaran into the house to retrieve his money. Kameshwaran is mistaken for Raju by Shalini who then tries to get intimate with him. Thirupu and her grandmother drag Kameshwaran away from her. Shalini then witnesses Kameshwaran hugging Thirupu. This enrages her as she thinks that Raju is two-timing her. To add to the hilarity, Chakkubai and Gangubai also arrive at the house in search of Madhan.\n\nChakkubai mistakes Kameshwaran for Madhan and introduces herself to everyone as Madhan's fianc\u00e9e, much to Avinashi's dismay, as his plan of using Kameshwaran to access Madhan's money keeps getting comically disrupted first by Raju's then by Madhan's girlfriend. Shalini takes a hunting rifle and holds everyone at gunpoint. Avinashi and the rest try to tell her that Kameshwaran is not Madhan/Raju but she does not believe them. Meanwhile, the real Madhan has escaped the cabin with his parents and comes to the house. In the midst of all this confusion, Michael steals Madhan's wealth and escapes to the cabin. The rest of the crew follows them back to the cabin in multiple cars.\n\nRamu and Nandagopal are already present in the cabin and hold everyone at gunpoint as they arrive one by one. All four brothers are finally in the same room at the same time and Sushila tells them that they are her quadruplets. The presence of all the people in the small cabin causes it to tilt over the cliff edge. The bad men are knocked out and the four brothers work together to safely get everyone out of the cabin. Everyone is happy as they are finally together.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] as Michael, Madhanagopal, Kameshwaran and Subramaniam Raju\n* [[R. N. Krishna Prasad]] as Venugopal<ref name=\"thenewsminute\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/what-makes-michael-madana-kama-rajan-finest-tamil-comedy-till-date-51521 |title=What makes \u2018Michael Madana Kama Rajan\u2019 the finest Tamil comedy till date |date=17 October 2016 |work=The News Minute |access-date=27 September 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Jayabharathi]] as Sushila\n* [[R. N. Jayagopal]] as Nandagopal\n* [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Ramgopal\n* [[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]] as Thiripurasundari<ref>{{Cite news |last=Vasudevan |first=K. V. |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/A-filmy-reunion/article16706323.ece |title=A filmy reunion |date=26 November 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=21 September 2017 |language=en-IN |issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n* [[Rupini (actress)|Rupini]] as ChakkuBai\n* [[Kushboo]] as Shalini Shivaraman\n* [[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]] as GangaBai<ref name=\"thenewsminute\" />\n* [[Delhi Ganesh]] as Palakkad Mani Iyer\n* [[Venniradai Moorthy]] as Shivaraman\n* [[S. N. Lakshmi]] as Thiripurasundari's grandmother\n* [[Nagesh]] as Avinashi<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/nagesh-a-stellar-comedian-news-tamil-kkfsxGbiaafsi.html |title=Nagesh, a stellar comedian |work=Sify |access-date=27 September 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Praveen Kumar (actor)|Praveen Kumar]] as Bheem, Madhan's Personal Assistant\n* [[Santhana Bharathi]] as Michael's foster father\n* [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]] as Travelling Singer\n* [[Crazy Mohan]] as Shop Owner\n* [[Ponnambalam (actor)|Ponnambalam]] as Assassin\n* Crazy Venkatesh as Assassin\n* [[R. S. Shivaji]]\n* [[Typist Gopu]]\n* [[Mayilsamy]]\n* [[Pradeep Shakthi]]\n* Usilai Mani{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Casting ===\nAccording to Singeetham, ''Michael Madana Kamarajan'' is a \"modern version of the old folk tale of a king, queen and their quadruplets who grow up in different households.\"<ref name=\"ss\">{{Cite web |url=https://silverscreen.in/features/interviews/singeetam-srinivasa-rao-interview-golden-rule-cinema-no-golden-rule/ |title=Singeetam Srinivasa Rao Interview: \u201cThe Golden Rule Of Cinema Is That There Is No Golden Rule\u201d |last=29 October |first=Aswathy Gopalakrishnan On |last2=2016 |date=29 October 2016}}</ref> Kamal Haasan played four distinct characters who are quadruplets: the criminal Michael, the businessman Madhan, the cook Kameshwaran and the firefighter Raju. For portraying Michael, Haasan grew his hair long and sported a [[French beard]]; for Madhan, he wore glasses and was clean-shaven; for Kameshwaran (also clean-shaven), he brushed his hair back and applied a ''vibhuti tilaka'' on his forehead; for Raju, he kept his mustache thick and hair short.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XDiv2uFwbIwC&pg=PA53&lpg=PA53&dq=indian+kamal+senapathy+chandru&source=bl&ots=Wpy1aHGYLZ&sig=sUhucVntKMWhWVz2cNYzttjGoPU&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwie-ef3z-vRAhUFLo8KHQ8sDeI4ChDoAQgqMAQ#v=onepage&q=indian%20kamal%20senapathy%20chandru&f=false |title=Southscope July 2010&nbsp;\u2013 Side A |date=July 2010 |website=[[Southscope]] |pages=52 |access-date=31 January 2017}}</ref> [[Praveen Kumar (actor)|Praveen Kumar]] was cast as Madhan's bodyguard Bheem.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/michael-madana-kamarajan/cast/ |title=Michael Madana Kamarajan |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |access-date=6 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nThe song \"Sundari Neeyum\" was filmed entirely in slow-motion with 48 frames.<ref name=ss /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Ramnath |first=Nandini |url=https://thereel.scroll.in/829592/picture-the-song-sundari-neeyum-is-a-slo-mo-beauty |title=Picture the song: \u2018Sundari Neeyum\u2019 is a slo-mo beauty |date=19 February 2017 |work=Scroll.in |access-date=31 August 2017 |language=en-US}}</ref> Singeetham initially wanted the picturisation with 20 widows in background however he changed the idea after hearing the tune of the song.<ref name=ss /> The climax sequence, featuring a \"cliff-hanging-house\", was based on a similar scene from the American film ''[[The Gold Rush]]'' (1925).<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kamath |first=Sudhish |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/04/stories/2008010450730200.htm |title=No, thank you! -- Welcome |date=4 January 2008 |work=[[The Hindu]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130125135400/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/04/stories/2008010450730200.htm |archive-date=25 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://kungumam.co.in/VArticalinnerdetail.aspx?id=1715&id1=40&issue=20120604 |title=\u0b86\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b8e\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f 100 \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd |date=4 June 2012 |work=Kungumam |access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref> The exterior portion was shot in Coonoor and the interior of the house was shot in studio, in a hydraulic set.<ref name=ss />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Michael Mathana Kama Rajan\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| released   = 1990\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| label      = Echo\n| language   = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| length     = \n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|xD_QEGC9PmI|Audio Jukebox Tamil}}\n | audio2     = {{YouTube|3BTeY6t3eo0|Audio Jukebox Telugu}}\n}}\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack consists of five memorable songs composed by [[Ilayaraja]]. [[K. J. Yesudas]] was supposed to sing ''Sundari Neeyum'', but due to his busy schedule Ilaiyaraaja insisted on Kamal Hassan singing the song.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/and-more-on-the-ilaiyaraaja-connection/article6379569.ece |title=And more on the Ilaiyaraaja connection |last=Rangan |first=Baradwaj |date=4 September 2014 |website=The Hindu |access-date=28 September 2017}}</ref> \"Rum Bum Bum\" is yet another fast melody and is a huge hit in college setting till date.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.musicindiaonline.com/music/tamil/s/movie_name.4851/ |title=Michael Madhana Kama Rajan (1990) |website=Music India Online |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090220131645/http://www.musicindiaonline.com/music/tamil/s/movie_name.4851 |archive-date=20 February 2009 |access-date=5 February 2009}}</ref> The soundtrack also had two songs \"Mathapoovu Oru Penna\" and \"Aadi Pattam Thedi\" which were not picturised.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-7Xnl2M6dD0 |title=Mathaapoovu Oru Pennaa -- Michael Madana Kamarajan (Unfeatured Song) |last=Venkateswaran Ganesan |date=10 January 2015 |via=YouTube |access-date=28 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3zwf6XbIMwI |title=Aadi Pattam Thedi Sennel... A rare gem of Ilayaraaja&nbsp;\u2014 Envazhi spl |last=Envazhi |date=21 August 2012 |via=YouTube |access-date=28 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1 = Kadha Kelu Kadha Kelu\n| note1 = \n| extra1 = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Panju Arunachalam]]\n| length1 = \n| title2 = Rum Bum Bum Arambum\n| note2 = \n| extra2 = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[K. S. Chithra]]\n| lyrics2 = [[Vaali (poet)|Vaali]]\n| length2 = \n| title3 = Siva Rathiri\n| note3 = \n| extra3 = K. S. Chithra, [[Mano (singer)|Mano]]\n| lyrics3 = Vaali\n| length3 = \n| title4 = Sundhari Neeyum Sundharan Njanum\n| note4 = \n| extra4 = [[Kamal Haasan]], [[S. Janaki]]\n| lyrics4 = [[Panju Arunachalam]]\n| length4 = \n| title5 = Vechalum Vekkama Ponnalum\n| note5 = \n| extra5 = [[Malaysia Vasudevan]], S. Janaki\n| lyrics5 = Vaali\n| length5 = \n| title6 = Mathapoovu Oru Penna\n| note6 = \n| extra6 = K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics6 = Vaali\n| length6 = \n| title7 = Aadi Pattam Thedi\n| note7 = \n| extra7 = Mano, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics7 = Vaali\n| length7 = \n| all_writing = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\n=== Telugu Track list ===\nThe film was dubbed into Telugu with the same title. [[Ilayaraja]] composed the music with [[Rajashri]] penning all the lyrics.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Telugu Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1  = Kadha Chebutha\n| note1   = \n| extra1  = [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Rajashri]]\n| length1 = \n| title2  = Rum Bum Bum Arambum\n| note2   = \n| extra2  = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[K. S. Chithra]]\n| lyrics2 = Rajashri\n| length2 = \n| title3  = Siva Rathiri\n| note3   = \n| extra3  = S.P.Balasubrahmanyam, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics3 = Rajashri\n| length3 = \n| title4  = Sundharudeevu Sundari Nenu\n| note4   = \n| extra4  = S.P.Balasubrahmanyam, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics4 = Rajashri\n| length4 = \n| title5  = Ee Kerintha\n| note5   = \n| extra5  = S.P.Balasubrahmanyam, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics5 = Rajashri\n| length5 = \n}}\n\n== Legacy ==\nSinger [[Mahathi]] said, \"I have always loved the \u2018Crazy\u2019 Mohan and Kamal Hassan combination. Especially in ''Michael Madana Kamarajan'' where Kamal brings out so much from every character, playing it so different from the other.\"<ref>{{Cite news |last=Mahathi |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/01/25/stories/2008012550120400.htm |title=Why I like... Michael Madana Kamarajan |date=25 January 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 September 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130125083606/http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/01/25/stories/2008012550120400.htm |archive-date=25 January 2013 |author-link=Mahathi}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0140377|title=Michael Madana Kama Rajan}}\n\n{{Singeetam Srinivasa Rao}}\n{{Kamal Haasan}}\n\n[[Category:1990 films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Tamil film scores by Ilaiyaraaja]]\n[[Category:1990s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Kamal Haasan]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Crazy Mohan]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1990 film by Singeetam Srinivasa Rao}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Michael Madana Kama Rajan\n| image          = Michael Madana Kama Rajan.jpg\n| alt            = L to R: Madhan and Chakkubai, Kameswaran and Thirupurasundari, Shalini and Raju\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]\n| producer       = Meena Panchu Arunachalam\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* [[Kamal Haasan]]\n* [[Crazy Mohan]] {{small|(dialogue)}}\n}}\n| story          = Kamal Haasan<br /> Kader Kashmiri\n| narrator       = \n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* Kamal Haasan\n* [[Urvashi (actress)|Urvasi]]\n* [[Rupini (actress)|Rupini]]\n* [[Kushboo]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cinematography = [[B. C. Gowrishankar]]\n| editing        = D. Vasu\n| studio         = [[Panchu Arunachalam|P. A. Art Productions]]\n| released       = 17 October 1990\n| runtime        = 167 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n\n'''''Michael Madana Kama Rajan''''' is a 1990 [[Tamil language]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]] and written by [[Kamal Haasan]], with [[Crazy Mohan]] penning the dialogues.\n\nThe film also feature a large [[ensemble cast]] alongside Kamal Haasan, [[Urvasi (actress)|Urvasi]], [[Rupini (actress)|Rupini]], [[Kushboo]] played the female leads, while [[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]], [[Delhi Ganesh]], [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]], [[Venniradai Moorthy]], [[SN Lakshmi]], [[Jayabharathi]], [[R. N. Jayagopal]], [[Nagesh]], [[Praveen Kumar (actor)|Praveen Kumar]] and [[Santhana Bharathi]] playing other significant roles. The film was a blockbuster and completed 175-day run at the box office.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nThe film tells a story of [[quadruplets]], Michael, Mathanagopal, Kameshwaran, and Raju, all played by Kamal Haasan. Kamal distinguished each of those characters with his body language and language lingo. Michael has a husky voice and an aggressive demeanor, Mathana has a [[British English|British accent]] with a sophisticated upper-class personality, Kameshwaran speaks [[Palakkad]] Tamil and has a naive, childish personality while Raju speaks [[Madras Tamil]] and has an outgoing, cheerful personality; all in keeping with their diverse upbringing as per the plot. The character played by an actress [[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]] was well received by the audience and still considered as one of the best comic role played ever by a heroine. The film was dubbed in Telugu as ''Michael Mathana Kama Raju''.\n\n== Plot ==\n{{Long plot|section|date=February 2017}}\n\nVenugopal is a wealthy industrialist. His wife Sushila gives birth to quadruplets, but his brother Nandagopal sends goons to kill the four children. But the leader of the goons doesn't want to kill the babies, so he adopts one (Michael), leaves one in an orphanage (Raju), one in a temple (Kameshwaran) who is picked by Palakkad Mani Iyer, and one (Madhan) in a car that belongs to Venugopal.\n\n30 years later, Madhan is now a London-educated businessman and the \"adopted\" son of Venugopal. He returns from London after his father's death to take over the business. But unbeknownst to him, Venugopal's car accident was planned by Nandagopal and Ramu for the want of his father's property. But Venugopal's will has named Madhan as the heir to all his wealth. \n\nMeanwhile, Michael has become a petty criminal like his foster father. While escaping from the police, they accidentally cause a fire in an art gallery where an artist Shalini is conducting an exhibition. A firefighter Raju saves Shalini and her paintings, and they fall in love after she gifts him a rice painting of Taj Mahal. \n\nKameshwaran is introduced as a cook for weddings and special events. He meets Thirupurasundari and her kleptomaniac grandmother. After a series of hilarious interactions, Kameshwaran and Thirupu fall in love and their wedding is being arranged\n\nAn unknown woman telephones Madhan tells him that his father's death was not an accident, and asks him to meet her in Chennai. After being distracted by a young girl named Chakkubai and her mother Gangubai, Madhan finally meets Sushila who called him. But he doesn't know that she is his real mother. \n\nWhile escaping from goons sent by Nandagopal and Ramu, Madhan meets Raju who fights the goons and saves him. He asks Raju to impersonate him for a while in Bangalore till he investigates his father's death in Chennai. Raju (while pretending to be Madhan) meets Shalini and her father who are also going to Bangalore, and invites them to stay with him. \n\nMichael is hired to kill Madhan and finds out that he is in Chennai. Meanwhile Madhan and Chakkubai have fallen in love and he presents her with a ring, but they are spied on by Michael and his father. Sushila meets Madhan again and reveals that his father in alive but is mentally unstable after the accident. Michael and his foster father arrive at the scene and kidnap all of them to a mountain cabin near Bangalore.\n\nOn the day of Kameshwaran's wedding, Avinashi sees him and asks him to impersonate Madhan to get 6 lakhs from his locker. Back in Madhan's house in Bangalore,\nRaju and Shalini meet and profess their love for one another. Michael (also dressed as Madhan) and his father arrive at Madhan's house to loot it. Michael sees Raju, mistakes him for Madhan and thinks that Madhan has escaped from the cabin. He knocks Raju unconscious. \n\nAvinashi sees the unconscious Raju, assumes it was the effect of his drugged soup, and brings Kameshwaran into the house to retrieve his money. Kameshwaran is mistaken for Raju by Shalini who then tries to get intimate with him. Thirupu and her grandmother drag Kameshwaran away from her. Shalini then witnesses Kameshwaran hugging Thirupu. This enrages her as she thinks that Raju is two-timing her. To add to the hilarity, Chakkubai and Gangubai also arrive at the house in search of Madhan.\n\nChakkubai mistakes Kameshwaran for Madhan and introduces herself to everyone as Madhan's fianc\u00e9e, much to Avinashi's dismay, as his plan of using Kameshwaran to access Madhan's money keeps getting comically disrupted first by Raju's then by Madhan's girlfriend. Shalini takes a hunting rifle and holds everyone at gunpoint. Avinashi and the rest try to tell her that Kameshwaran is not Madhan/Raju but she does not believe them. Meanwhile, the real Madhan has escaped the cabin with his parents and comes to the house. In the midst of all this confusion, Michael steals Madhan's wealth and escapes to the cabin. The rest of the crew follows them back to the cabin in multiple cars.\n\nRamu and Nandagopal are already present in the cabin and hold everyone at gunpoint as they arrive one by one. All four brothers are finally in the same room at the same time and Sushila tells them that they are her quadruplets. The presence of all the people in the small cabin causes it to tilt over the cliff edge. The bad men are knocked out and the four brothers work together to safely get everyone out of the cabin. Everyone is happy as they are finally together.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] as Michael, Madhanagopal, Kameshwaran and Subramaniam Raju\n* [[R. N. Krishna Prasad]] as Venugopal<ref name=\"thenewsminute\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/what-makes-michael-madana-kama-rajan-finest-tamil-comedy-till-date-51521 |title=What makes \u2018Michael Madana Kama Rajan\u2019 the finest Tamil comedy till date |date=17 October 2016 |work=The News Minute |access-date=27 September 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Jayabharathi]] as Sushila\n* [[R. N. Jayagopal]] as Nandagopal\n* [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Ramgopal\n* [[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]] as Thiripurasundari<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/A-filmy-reunion/article16706323.ece |title=A filmy reunion |last=Vasudevan |first=K. V. |date=26 November 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=21 September 2017 |language=en-IN |issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n* [[Rupini (actress)|Rupini]] as ChakkuBai\n* [[Kushboo]] as Shalini Shivaraman\n* [[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]] as GangaBai<ref name=\"thenewsminute\" />\n* [[Delhi Ganesh]] as Palakkad Mani Iyer\n* [[Venniradai Moorthy]] as Shivaraman\n* [[S. N. Lakshmi]] as Thiripurasundari's grandmother\n* [[Nagesh]] as Avinashi<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/nagesh-a-stellar-comedian-news-tamil-kkfsxGbiaafsi.html |title=Nagesh, a stellar comedian |work=Sify |access-date=27 September 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Praveen Kumar (actor)|Praveen Kumar]] as Bheem, Madhan's Personal Assistant\n* [[Santhana Bharathi]] as Michael's foster father\n* [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]] as Travelling Singer\n* [[Crazy Mohan]] as Shop Owner\n* [[Ponnambalam (actor)|Ponnambalam]] as Assassin\n* Crazy Venkatesh as Assassin\n* [[R. S. Shivaji]]\n* [[Typist Gopu]]\n* [[Mayilsamy]]\n* [[Pradeep Shakthi]]\n* Usilai Mani{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Casting ===\nAccording to Singeetham, ''Michael Madana Kamarajan'' is a \"modern version of the old folk tale of a king, queen and their quadruplets who grow up in different households.\"<ref name=\"ss\">{{Cite web |url=https://silverscreen.in/features/interviews/singeetam-srinivasa-rao-interview-golden-rule-cinema-no-golden-rule/ |title=Singeetam Srinivasa Rao Interview: \u201cThe Golden Rule Of Cinema Is That There Is No Golden Rule\u201d |last=29 October |first=Aswathy Gopalakrishnan On |last2=2016 |date=29 October 2016}}</ref> Kamal Haasan played four distinct characters who are quadruplets: the criminal Michael, the businessman Madhan, the cook Kameshwaran and the firefighter Raju. For portraying Michael, Haasan grew his hair long and sported a [[French beard]]; for Madhan, he wore glasses and was clean-shaven; for Kameshwaran (also clean-shaven), he brushed his hair back and applied a ''vibhuti tilaka'' on his forehead; for Raju, he kept his mustache thick and hair short.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XDiv2uFwbIwC&pg=PA53&lpg=PA53&dq=indian+kamal+senapathy+chandru&source=bl&ots=Wpy1aHGYLZ&sig=sUhucVntKMWhWVz2cNYzttjGoPU&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwie-ef3z-vRAhUFLo8KHQ8sDeI4ChDoAQgqMAQ#v=onepage&q=indian%20kamal%20senapathy%20chandru&f=false |title=Southscope July 2010&nbsp;\u2013 Side A |date=July 2010 |website=[[Southscope]] |pages=52 |access-date=31 January 2017}}</ref> [[Praveen Kumar (actor)|Praveen Kumar]] was cast as Madhan's bodyguard Bheem.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/michael-madana-kamarajan/cast/ |title=Michael Madana Kamarajan |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |access-date=6 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nThe song \"Sundari Neeyum\" was filmed entirely in slow-motion with 48 frames.<ref name=ss /><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://thereel.scroll.in/829592/picture-the-song-sundari-neeyum-is-a-slo-mo-beauty |title=Picture the song: \u2018Sundari Neeyum\u2019 is a slo-mo beauty |last=Ramnath |first=Nandini |date=19 February 2017 |work=Scroll.in |access-date=31 August 2017 |language=en-US}}</ref> Singeetham initially wanted the picturisation with 20 widows in background however he changed the idea after hearing the tune of the song.<ref name=ss /> The climax sequence, featuring a \"cliff-hanging-house\", was based on a similar scene from the American film ''[[The Gold Rush]]'' (1925).<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/04/stories/2008010450730200.htm |title=No, thank you! -- Welcome |last=Kamath |first=Sudhish |date=4 January 2008 |work=[[The Hindu]] |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130125135400/http://www.hindu.com/fr/2008/01/04/stories/2008010450730200.htm |archive-date=25 January 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://kungumam.co.in/VArticalinnerdetail.aspx?id=1715&id1=40&issue=20120604 |title=\u0b86\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b8e\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f 100 \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd |date=4 June 2012 |work=Kungumam |access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref> The exterior portion was shot in Coonoor and the interior of the house was shot in studio, in a hydraulic set.<ref name=ss />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Michael Mathana Kama Rajan\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| released   = 1990\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| label      = Echo\n| language   = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| length     = \n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|xD_QEGC9PmI|Audio Jukebox Tamil}}\n | audio2     = {{YouTube|3BTeY6t3eo0|Audio Jukebox Telugu}}\n}}\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack consists of five memorable songs composed by [[Ilayaraja]]. [[K. J. Yesudas]] was supposed to sing ''Sundari Neeyum'', but due to his busy schedule Ilaiyaraaja insisted on Kamal Hassan singing the song.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/and-more-on-the-ilaiyaraaja-connection/article6379569.ece |title=And more on the Ilaiyaraaja connection |last=Rangan |first=Baradwaj |date=4 September 2014 |website=The Hindu |access-date=28 September 2017}}</ref> \"Rum Bum Bum\" is yet another fast melody and is a huge hit in college setting till date.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.musicindiaonline.com/music/tamil/s/movie_name.4851/ |title=Michael Madhana Kama Rajan (1990) |work=Music India Online |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090220131645/http://www.musicindiaonline.com/music/tamil/s/movie_name.4851 |archive-date=20 February 2009 |access-date=5 February 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The soundtrack also had two songs \"Mathapoovu Oru Penna\" and \"Aadi Pattam Thedi\" which were not picturised.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-7Xnl2M6dD0 |title=Mathaapoovu Oru Pennaa -- Michael Madana Kamarajan (Unfeatured Song) |last=Venkateswaran Ganesan |date=10 January 2015 |via=YouTube |access-date=28 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3zwf6XbIMwI |title=Aadi Pattam Thedi Sennel... A rare gem of Ilayaraaja&nbsp;\u2014 Envazhi spl |last=Envazhi |date=21 August 2012 |via=YouTube |access-date=28 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1 = Kadha Kelu Kadha Kelu\n| note1 = \n| extra1 = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Panju Arunachalam]]\n| length1 = \n| title2 = Rum Bum Bum Arambum\n| note2 = \n| extra2 = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[K. S. Chithra]]\n| lyrics2 = [[Vaali (poet)|Vaali]]\n| length2 = \n| title3 = Siva Rathiri\n| note3 = \n| extra3 = K. S. Chithra, [[Mano (singer)|Mano]]\n| lyrics3 = Vaali\n| length3 = \n| title4 = Sundhari Neeyum Sundharan Njanum\n| note4 = \n| extra4 = [[Kamal Haasan]], [[S. Janaki]]\n| lyrics4 = [[Panju Arunachalam]]\n| length4 = \n| title5 = Vechalum Vekkama Ponnalum\n| note5 = \n| extra5 = [[Malaysia Vasudevan]], S. Janaki\n| lyrics5 = Vaali\n| length5 = \n| title6 = Mathapoovu Oru Penna\n| note6 = \n| extra6 = K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics6 = Vaali\n| length6 = \n| title7 = Aadi Pattam Thedi\n| note7 = \n| extra7 = Mano, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics7 = Vaali\n| length7 = \n| all_writing = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\n=== Telugu Track list ===\nThe film was dubbed into Telugu with the same title. [[Ilayaraja]] composed the music with [[Rajashri]] penning all the lyrics.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Telugu Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1  = Kadha Chebutha\n| note1   = \n| extra1  = [[Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Rajashri]]\n| length1 = \n| title2  = Rum Bum Bum Arambum\n| note2   = \n| extra2  = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[K. S. Chithra]]\n| lyrics2 = Rajashri\n| length2 = \n| title3  = Siva Rathiri\n| note3   = \n| extra3  = S.P.Balasubrahmanyam, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics3 = Rajashri\n| length3 = \n| title4  = Sundharudeevu Sundari Nenu\n| note4   = \n| extra4  = S.P.Balasubrahmanyam, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics4 = Rajashri\n| length4 = \n| title5  = Ee Kerintha\n| note5   = \n| extra5  = S.P.Balasubrahmanyam, K. S. Chithra\n| lyrics5 = Rajashri\n| length5 = \n}}\n\n== Legacy ==\nSinger [[Mahathi]] said, \"I have always loved the \u2018Crazy\u2019 Mohan and Kamal Hassan combination. Especially in ''Michael Madana Kamarajan'' where Kamal brings out so much from every character, playing it so different from the other.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/01/25/stories/2008012550120400.htm |title=Why I like... Michael Madana Kamarajan |last=Mahathi |date=25 January 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 September 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130125083606/http://www.hindu.com/cp/2008/01/25/stories/2008012550120400.htm |archive-date=25 January 2013 |author-link=Mahathi |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0140377|title=Michael Madana Kama Rajan}}\n\n{{Singeetam Srinivasa Rao}}\n{{Kamal Haasan}}\n\n[[Category:1990 films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Tamil film scores by Ilaiyaraaja]]\n[[Category:1990s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Singeetam Srinivasa Rao]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Kamal Haasan]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Crazy Mohan]]\n", "name_user": "Kailash29792", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reference edited withProveIt", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Madana_Kama_Rajan"}
